WEBVTT

00:01.174 --> 00:04.455
Do you believe that
a deity can hear our prayers?

00:04.539 --> 00:06.850
Or is it a divine force
that created our universe?

00:06.920 --> 00:08.167
Did that chick spray you with something?

00:08.251 --> 00:09.752
Here's a list of the labs using

00:09.836 --> 00:12.517
a South Korean stem cell line
for disease related gene therapy.

00:12.657 --> 00:15.299
Ok, Wes, tell me the truth.
How much time do I have to finish my work?

00:15.383 --> 00:16.759
The clock's ticking.

00:18.285 --> 00:19.429
Shit!

00:19.512 --> 00:22.348
I think the South Korean stem
cell line is producing a retrovirus.

00:22.535 --> 00:23.723
What?

00:23.791 --> 00:25.356
Ok, what kind of virus
are we talking about?

00:25.435 --> 00:28.950
Don't know. Could give you
the sniffles, could be the next AIDS.

00:29.444 --> 00:31.315
When I talk to Glenn,
I can feel him listening.

00:31.568 --> 00:33.590
So, we're going to go
for a jog in Central Park.

00:34.655 --> 00:37.383
Why would there be
a farm in the subway?

00:37.626 --> 00:41.112
Why would someone want
to grow something in a subway?

00:41.288 --> 00:44.412
Because you wouldn't want
anyone to know what you were growing.

00:44.458 --> 00:47.663
Marijuana, Psilocybin
Mushrooms, Opium...

00:47.745 --> 00:49.250
They got a grow op down there.

00:49.337 --> 00:50.963
Dude, I can't get rid of it, it's not mine.

00:51.095 --> 00:52.823
It's the people or the pot, Owen.

00:53.158 --> 00:54.253
Hi, dad.

00:54.336 --> 00:56.130
She's not here any more, David.

00:56.218 --> 00:57.432
My mom was an orphan,

00:57.536 --> 01:00.132
so there is silence
on that side of the family.

01:00.306 --> 01:01.720
My dad is Swedish.

01:01.807 --> 01:04.343
Which is major silence.
I was an only child.

01:04.787 --> 01:06.763
You know, maybe it's time you
let her off the hook, Dad.

01:07.016 --> 01:08.211
Why should I?

01:10.686 --> 01:12.621
Because she's dead, Dad.

01:13.725 --> 01:14.900
Mom...

01:15.677 --> 01:17.623
I will miss you every day

01:18.678 --> 01:21.072
for the rest of my life.

01:22.868 --> 01:24.912
Come on, Dad.
I'll make you some dinner.

01:25.486 --> 01:26.923
That's your mother's job.

01:27.088 --> 01:29.132
She doesn't like anybody
else in the kitchen.

01:32.717 --> 01:34.751
<i>Xylella fastidiosa.</i>

01:35.216 --> 01:36.960
In Brazil, it's responsible

01:37.058 --> 01:39.950
for the destruction
of over 34 % of the citrus crop.

01:40.118 --> 01:43.140
Isn't Brazil a little out
of our jurisdiction?

01:43.285 --> 01:45.401
It is. Florida isn't.

01:47.438 --> 01:51.043
Salvador Charringa has over
10,000 acres of citrus groves

01:51.257 --> 01:53.563
- outside Miami...
- The same Salvador Charringa

01:53.648 --> 01:56.643
who openly admits he helped
finance the Bay of Pigs.

01:56.838 --> 01:59.351
He lost a lot when
he was exiled by Castro.

01:59.695 --> 02:02.173
10,000 acres of Florida oranges:

02:02.367 --> 02:05.250
- looks like he landed on his feet.
- Not quite.

02:05.866 --> 02:09.412
This is what 1,500 of those acres

02:10.038 --> 02:11.943
looked like as of last week.

02:12.168 --> 02:15.332
Charringa's scientists are claiming

02:15.787 --> 02:18.682
it's a biologically engineered
form of the bacterium

02:18.905 --> 02:21.270
and the only cure for it
is to kill the patient.

02:21.417 --> 02:23.221
What are we talking about?
Agricultural terrorism?

02:23.397 --> 02:26.142
A little over 2 months ago, 3 teenagers
where caught in Charringa's grove.

02:26.408 --> 02:29.300
They admitted taking money
to release a dozen crates

02:29.446 --> 02:31.353
of an insect called
a leafhopper into his--

02:31.566 --> 02:34.030
- Could you be more specific?
- More specific?

02:35.427 --> 02:39.193
- It was a sharpshooter leafhopper.
- Oh, that makes sense.

02:39.618 --> 02:40.950
What makes sense?

02:41.068 --> 02:43.612
Well it explains why
the bacterium is spreading so fast.

02:43.698 --> 02:47.852
<i>See, the X. fastidiosa bacterium
multiplies in the foregut</i>

02:47.997 --> 02:50.121
of the sharpshooter. Then they spread it

02:50.165 --> 02:52.120
from tree to tree
where it multiplies again

02:52.205 --> 02:53.753
and then other
sharpshooters pick it up

02:53.836 --> 02:55.753
and they pass it on to other trees...

02:55.835 --> 02:57.583
Did those kids say who paid them?

02:57.675 --> 02:59.500
Quote. "Old Cuban dudes

02:59.545 --> 03:03.422
with bad breath and real shiny shoes."
End quote.

03:03.506 --> 03:05.130
That sounds pretty thin, Connor.

03:05.328 --> 03:08.093
Charringa made it thick
enough to convince the US.

03:08.186 --> 03:09.973
to demand an inspection

03:10.018 --> 03:12.512
of Cuba's Center for Genetic
Engineering and Biotechnology.

03:13.006 --> 03:14.681
- And?
- It came up clean.

03:14.775 --> 03:16.342
So what's the problem?

03:17.358 --> 03:20.983
The US has insisted
upon looking at 7 other suspected labs.

03:21.065 --> 03:22.823
And Cuba doesn't want
to play along anymore.

03:22.906 --> 03:25.533
They're claiming the old labs
are nothing but empty shells.

03:25.858 --> 03:27.362
According to some experts,

03:27.458 --> 03:30.910
Florida could be on the verge of
a plague of biblical proportions.

03:31.855 --> 03:33.921
We'd like to know if it's God's will

03:34.188 --> 03:35.801
or Fidel's?

